RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 1 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 85. Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO 30% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 18, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON THREE RACES IN 2022 - 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLAWLESS BOURBON tracked three deep through the first turn, tacked to the rail on the backstretch, slipped through and forged command after a half, shook clear on the second turn and held sway under steady urging. AULT attended the pace along the inside, shifted out leaving the quarter pole to launch her bid, kicked on well but was unable to reach the winner. SPETTACOLI (ARG) tucked in to save ground on the first turn, got through every step and churned on to earn the minor award. BELIEVEINHOLIDAYS contested the pace off of the inside, relinquished the lead after a half, stayed on to the final furlong and faded. SNAKERATTLEANDROLL was allowed to settle, came under a ride on the second turn, came four wide and finished with a belated improvement. KING OF THE RING failed to respond. BOOMIN GOOSE vied for the lead three wide to the second turn and dropped out.
